slre
------------------------------------------
SLRE is an ISO C library that implements a subset of Perl regular expression
syntax.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.0.7-1
  libslre-devel-1.3-1bl2
  libslre0-1.3-1bl2
  pkg-config-1.6.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-10-1
  binutils-2.29-1
  cygport-0.33.1-1
  gcc-core-7.4.0-1
  libtool-2.4.6-6
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/cesanta/slre

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/cesanta/slre/archive/1.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack slre-1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./slre-1.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/slre-1.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/slre-1.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libslre0-1.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libslre-devel-1.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(slre)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/slre.README
  /usr/share/doc/slre/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/slre/README.md

(libslre0)
  /usr/bin/cygslre-0.dll

(libslre-devel)
  /usr/include/slre.h
  /usr/lib/libslre.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/slre.pc

------------------

Port Notes:

----- version 1.3-1bl2 -----
Rebuild with gcc-7.4.0

